<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
    <head>
        <title>Jeong Won Kim Portfolio</title>
        <link rel="icon" href="/img/icon.jpg">
        <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/styles.css">
    </head>
    <body>
        <div class="main">
            {{>header}}
            <div class="main-content">
                {{>sidemenu}}
                <div class="centered-form">
                    <div class="explanation">
                        <h4>Github Link: <a href="https://github.com/KumamonRiceCake/weather-forecast-nodejs" target="_blank">https://github.com/KumamonRiceCake/weather-forecast-nodejs</a></h4>
                        <h4>App on Heroku: <a href="https://kim-weather-forecast-app.herokuapp.com/" target="_blank">https://kim-weather-forecast-app.herokuapp.com/</a></h4>
                        <img class="app-image" src="/img/weather2.png" width="500" height="270">
                        <img class="app-image" src="/img/weather3.png" width="500" height="270">
                        <h3>Features</h3>
                        <p>This simple node.js application lets users <b>search weather information</b> of their current location or desired location.</p>
                        <p>It requests data from <b>location API</b> provided by <a href="https://www.mapbox.com/" target="_blank">https://www.mapbox.com/</a> and <b>weather API</b> provided by <a href="https://weatherstack.com/" target="_blank">https://weatherstack.com/.</a></p>
                        <br>
                        <h3>How to use</h3>
                        <p>To search weather information of the desired location, type search term in the text box and click the 'Search' button or press enter key.</p>
                        <p>To see weather information of current location, click the 'My location' button.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </body>
</html>